\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Bullo }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, you\u8217\'92ve got to get thinking about it. When you don\u8217\'92t have the time to work hard, you\u8217\'92ve got to work smart. So let\u8217\'92s get you thinking about it. First, you got to define your goal. What is your goal in a fight with blades?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Survive.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hah! Good! That\u8217\'92s right! Usually folk say its to kill your opponent, but that excludes a perfectly viable strategy in any fight: running away.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can do that.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Right! You should always run away, if you can. I\u8217\'92m not just saying that because you\u8217\'92re inexperienced. If you pulled a blade on me, I\u8217\'92d run away. If it came to blows I\u8217\'92d kill you a hundred times out of a hundred, if it came to it, but I\u8217\'92d still prefer run away.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Because swords are sharp, Pyetle. You ever been cut? I mean }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 really}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  cut. Doesn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t take much for a blade like that to find the bone.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But you said that -\u8220\'93}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, I said a hundred times out of a hundred. But a thousand times? A hundred thousand? You\u8217\'92d get lucky in a few of those. The point is that there\u8217\'92s always risk and it\u8217\'92s never worth taking if you can just, simply, run away. I\u8217\'92ve seen men as skilled as the caliphants of legend get stabbed in the belly by raw recruits. It just happens sometimes. Especially when you\u8217\'92re getting long in the tooth. You understand, eh? Can\u8217\'92t get away with things you used to.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Believe me, I don\u8217\'92t need lessons in running away.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Bullo chuckled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sure. Sure. So, in the event you }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 can\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92t }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 run away, the goal becomes clearer than simply surviving.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Kill you before you kill me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You could settle for incapacitate.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Suppose I could.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A lot of killing blows don\u8217\'92t kill quickly. There\u8217\'92s a few reliable spots. The heart,\u8221\'94 He pounded his chest. \u8220\'93And the head.\u8221\'94 He tapped his skull. \u8220\'93Of course you\u8217\'92ve got to consider armor in all this. It\u8217\'92s why Imperial Socars wear breastplates and helmets and not much else. Commissars will say that the reason they don\u8217\'92t outfit the troops with more protection is because there\u8217\'92s not enough iron to go around, but really it\u8217\'92s just because the Empire can afford one to one trades. When a Socar\u8217\'92s life gets cut down to minutes, he\u8217\'92s taught to spend them with reckless abandon, to do whatever he can to make sure the enemy whose blade is stuck in his belly goes down with him. You might not believe it, but they\u8217\'92ve got a whole discipline that teaches them how, if you get struck down this way or that, sword or spear, what\u8217\'92s the best thing to do to get \u8216\'91em back.\u8221\'94 The Empire can afford to think like that. They can afford one-for-one trades.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But Jandrians are mostly known for slings and arrows. .\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Pyetle, they can afford twenty-for-one trades. That, and they\u8217\'92ve got these things called shields\u8230\'85\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Right.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Anyways, the point is, if the goal is to incapacitate\u8230\'85. Well if we had more time we\u8217\'92d get into taking what they give you. Every style and stance is presenting something as a target. But for now let\u8217\'92s just say our target is the sword arm. Generally speaking, its the closest part of the enemy to your blade, and if struck, the threat is nullified. There\u8217\'92s three parts: shoulder, arm, and hand.\u8221\'94 He tapped each part as he was wont to do.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The hand is simple. It\u8217\'92s basically just a bundle tendon, muscle, and bone. If it gets cut anywhere, prettymuch, then the hand goes to shit. If I can\u8217\'92t grip my sword, you win.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pyetle nodded. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The hard part about the hand, is that its a small target that moves quickly. The shoulder however, is tied to the body\u8217\'92s core, and moves slowly. If I hack your shoulder here,\u8221\'94 He patted the meat of Pyetle shoulder, \u8220\'93You won\u8217\'92t drop your sword, but you won\u8217\'92t be able to raise it. You\u8217\'92ll still be able to stab with it, but swinging is out of the question. So remember that. Hit the shoulder and he can still stab. Of course, if you get lucky and sever the nerve here, then the whole arm goes to shit.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92d be lucky just to land a blow.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sure, sure. I know this is a lot to take in, but these things need to be rolling around in your brain. When the time comes, you\u8217\'92ll see, the mind has a way of digging these things up. Just remember the key things at least: Sword arm,\u8221\'94 he patted his own right arm. \u8220\'93Fast but near,\u8221\'94 he held up his hand. \u8220\'93Slow but far.\u8221\'94 He held the shoulder.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now, before we get into the technical side of attacking these points, we\u8217\'92ve got to touch a bit on the art of swordplay.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Never thought there was anything artful about killing. Brutal business.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93When I say art, I mean a way of thinking about solving problems. It\u8217\'92s something all the arts share. They all take one fundamental thing, like in music its a single note, in painting its a single brushstroke - they take this one thing, and they put a bunch of them together to form a more complex whole. In swordplay it\u8217\'92s no different. I\u8217\'92m sure you\u8217\'92ve heard it\u8217\'92s like dance because it is like dance - it\u8217\'92s using the same fundamental stuff to compose its many forms: and that\u8217\'92s the human body. When it comes down to it, swordplay, and fighting in general, well of course they\u8217\'92re artforms. They\u8217\'92re a genres of dance.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t understand.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You don\u8217\'92t need to. You just need to be thinking about it like this - and I\u8217\'92ll use music as an example because it\u8217\'92s familiar to everyone - music has certain aspects to it which the musician needs to be aware of if he wants to be a competent musician. There is melody, harmony rhythm, texture, how loud or soft it is. Every single note is affect all of this aspects of the song simultaneously. That\u8217\'92s the important thing. If you want to compose a song, you need to be thinking about how the next not you place is going to affect not just the melody, but also the harmony, the rhythm, the texture, the loudness, and more.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Again, it\u8217\'92s the same with all art forms. You paint a painting, with every single brushstroke, you\u8217\'92re making a statement about color, about edge, about value, and more. So if you\u8217\'92re a painter you need to be aware of those aspects. Every single brushtroke you make affects everything simultaneously.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So what\u8217\'92s the fundamental stuff in swordplay.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Its the human body. Well, the body and the sword as one.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, what are the, uh , If music has harmony and melody and whatnot -\u8220\'93}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes. Yes. what are the component parts of a duel? It\u8217\'92s these: distance, timing, balance, risk, sequence, and most importantly, the opposition.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I see.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Every movement you make affects all of these things simultaneously. I take a step towards you, and I am changing the distance. I am playing with risk. I have changed my center of balance. I am setting up a sequence, because with this step, whatever actions come next must flow from it, and then most importantly, of course, is what you, the opposition, does in turn.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can\u8217\'92t possibly be thinking about all these things. Not in the middle of a duel. There\u8217\'92s no time.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93These and more. Really theres no end to the aspects of any art, because after all, it\u8217\'92s all made up. Just stick with the basics, drill them, and you\u8217\'92ll be competent enough to hold your own.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Can\u8217\'92t you just show me a few moves?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s an art, Pyetle.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93An art? I\u8217\'92m not trying to express myself here. My aim is to survive.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know. But \u8216\'91a few moves\u8217\'92 aren\u8217\'92t going to keep you alive. You need to be able to react to whatever is going on. To do that you need to be able to solve novel problems. Creativity, Pyetle. Creativity is what will keep you alive. To be creative, you need to be thinking critically about what it is you\u8217\'92re doing. That\u8217\'92s what art is, that is what fighting is; creative problem solving. You need to be thinking this way and so we\u8217\'92ll practice it. Now stand up.\u8221\'94}
